quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  71,21,"And said NuH, .My Lord, they disobeyed me, and followed him whose wealth and children added nothing to him but loss"
  71,22,and they devised a mighty plot
  71,23,"and said (to their people), .Never forsake your gods, and never forsake Wadd, nor Suwa‘, nor Yaghuth and Ya‘uq and Nasr"
  71,24,"And they have led many astray. And (O my Lord,) let not the wrongdoers progress in anything but deviation from the right path"
  71,25,"Because of their sins they were drowned, and then admitted into the Fire. So they found no helpers for them besides Allah"
  71,26,"And said NuH, .My Lord, do not leave on earth even a single inhabitant (surviving) out of the disbelievers"
  71,27,"If You leave them (surviving), they will lead Your servants astray, and will beget none but a sinful disbeliever"
  71,28,"My Lord, grant pardon to me, and to my parents, and to everyone who enters my home as a believer, and to all the believing men and believing women, and do not increase the wrongdoers but in ruin"